data.title: Glo Dollar x Arbitrum DAO
data.description: We’re rallying all Web3 projects to start embedding philanthropy in their organization by integrating the Glo Dollar stablecoin in their platform and/or treasury. By doing so these organizations bring three benefits to the world: (1) directly contribute to funding basic incomes for people in extreme poverty, (2) spread the word about Glo Dollar to a bigger audience, indirectly growing basic income funding, and (3) opportunity to join the Glo Consortium to further collaborate on reducing extreme poverty. Glo Dollar is collaborating with Arbitrum DAO to bring a total of $10,000 in USDGLO in matching for organizations that embed philanthropy. Whether you're already part of the Glo Consortium or looking to dive into Glo, this round is for you.

data.text: Thx to this grant (used $400) and a supporter who provided $800 our founder was able to stay at ZuVillage Georgia during the week dedicated to Network States and did heavy networking there

The program took place from July 18th, 2024 to August 2nd, 2024 celebrating the 55th anniversary of Apollo's landing on the Moon

questions.query: How is the project CollabTech?
questions.explanation:
To implement WebRTC support we are seeking to raise $2000


[The Networking Module](https://github.com/LunCoSim/lunco-sim/blob/main/core/singletones/networking.gd) is already exists and works properly in binary builds, allowing to design and explore systems together with friends.


However it was to be updated to support [WebRTC](https://docs.godotengine.org/en/stable/tutorials/networking/webrtc.html) and provide networking expirience in browser builds, allowing to run collaborative missions directly from browsers

questions.query: Please describe how your project contributes to the growth and development of the Octant ecosystem.
questions.explanation:
LunCo is an opensource software for space systems engineering.

One of our main goals is to onboard Space Engineers into Web3 and Public Goods.

LunCo is an active participant in Regen activities, promoting them among Space Professionals, and we naturally shill Octant to them

questions.query: How does your project align with the round's focus on community and education within the Octant ecosystem?
questions.explanation: We are not just doing software for space missions simulations, but also onboarding Space Professionals into Public Goods Funding Ecoystem that naturally includes Octant

questions.query: Provide a clear roadmap of your project, detailing future milestones and deliverables. How does this demonstrate your commitment to long-term impact and growth within the Octant ecosystem?
questions.explanation:
### Development
- Update to Godot 4.4

- Networking support in Browser using webRTC

- Implement Rover controller to add rovers

- Login in Browser via Metamask and chat among logined persons

### BizDev
- Attend side events in Chiang Mai to establish more connection to Web3

- Present DeSpace at DeSci side events in BKK before DevCon

- Waiting for the confirmation from DevCon team to hold a DeSpace focused round table

By supporting us we would shill Octant at all the presentations that we are holding, as well as the round on our Socials + naturally we would share with Space Projects that are build in Public Octant as a way to support their activitis

questions.query: Describe your team's expertise and how it contributes to the successful execution of your project.
questions.explanation:
Our founder is a space systems engineer, he was responsible for engineering of the first [walking rover for the Moon](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Fko0VZNO8DM)

And an artwork that he engineered was send to [the Moon early this year](https://wired.me/culture/sacha-jafri-art-moon/#:~:text=In%20February%202022%2C%20Dubai%2Dbased,its%20way%20to%20the%20moon.)

questions.query: How does your project complement or enhance existing initiatives within the Octant ecosystem rather than competing directly against them?
questions.explanation:
We are focused on changing the way humanity does space exploration with tools to design space missions (as a core value to space professionals) and on top of that with regen web3 mecanics.

Basically it means that we are onboarding a very special audience into Public Goods in general, and naturally to Octant

questions.query: Describe your approach to community engagement and how you plan to contribute to a collaborative and constructive funding environment.
questions.explanation:
1. Our main project is a collaborative tool for space missions simulation inspired by existing highly propriatary systems

2. We are doing tons of IRL meetings with Space Projects, onboarding them one by one into Public Goods Funding ecosystem

questions.query: How do you plan to use the funding to maximize your project's ongoing impact within the Octant ecosystem if selected?
questions.explanation: Sustain our operations, deliver the next iteration of LunCoSim prototype (it'll take 3-6 months), and then keep shilling Public Goods at Web3 to Space projects.

questions.query: What unique educational content or resources have you created for the Octant ecosystem? How has the community received these? Please share any relevant links
questions.explanation: Mostly we shared Octant in IRl meetings as a way of funding public goods among space professionals, so no links

questions.query: How does your project contribute to the growth of the OSS ecosystem? Please provide specific examples of how your application enhances or expands the current ecosystem.
questions.explanation:
Our software is MIT licenced, based on MIT licenced Godot, meaning user could do whatever they want to do.

Our software is made for Space Engineers. We also have several early-staged open hardware projects for space, so we are bringing Opensource to the final frontier, as well as aiming to lower the cost of space missions, making them more affordable.

One of our goals is to also onboard space engineers into web3 by deep integration of the LunCoSim, starting with basic things like gating via NFT, adding and experementing with mechaincs like IP-NFT on the way using tools like token engineering.

questions.query: What features or use cases does your dApp/App present? How is it differentiated?
questions.explanation:
1. Login via wallet 
2. Tokengating access via Profile NFT
3. Missions NFT aka IP NFT for space missions
4. Integration with decentralized data storages for space data
5. Ultimately - protocol to design space missions + implementation in smart contracts

Our project is focused on very specific niche, with the idea to apply best practices from web3 to space projects, making it distinctive.

questions.query: What are your plans for further development, and how will the grant funds be used to achieve these goals?
questions.explanation:
1. Implement rover/vehicle controller to be able to create robots
2. Support of URDF to be able to import robots
3. Refactor Networking module to make it more robust
4. Finalize tokengating via Profile NFT
5. Implement Mission NFT - possibility to modify mission and publish it onchain
6. Solar system View - integration with ivoyager

Grant funds would help us sustain operations:
1. Compensation to contributors
2. Paying for services e.g. VPS, LLMs
3. Upgrading equipment (like laptop for developer)
